Her relationship with her brothers and sister is something so special to watch. She loves to pretend and tell stories and play games!She’s a nurturer by nature and is so tender with the boys (or anyone) when they are hurt.

Nothing like getting fancy and attending my first ever gala with my man. 😘🥰🥂

Tonight is special for me as a business woman. I’ve worked really hard on my business over the last couple years and this year I was nominated for the emerging business award. There will be a live vote tonight at the gala to see who wins, but honestly, just to be nominated means SO MUCH!! Thank you, Manistee, for supporting me and cheering on my small business! ❤️

I’m behind on posting the recent birthdays, but for anyone wondering if Emelia is still afraid of the sparkle candle… 😏 we have ourselves a big girl.

I missed a couple birthday posts. So I’m playing catch up now. I can’t believe the boys are 3!

They are hysterical. Their little personalities and relationship are so special. 

Whit will hold an intellectual conversation with you, he’s a rule follower, and protector, feisty, but he still has a very silly sense of humor. He’s my mommas boy FOR SURE. He can never get enough kisses and hugs.

Liam is my peanut goofball. He’s a prankster and has the biggest full face “crazy” smile. He loves to dance, play with trains, and pretend he’s a dog…. Yes he gives kisses by licking. It’s too cute to stop him. 🤷🏻‍♀️ He’s mommas little sidekick too. He wants to do everything with me. 

I had no idea I needed them so… but I guess that’s why God gives us surprises. 

Happy VERY belated birthday boys!

It seems like every year when the weather starts warming, we have a point where we can’t fight the urge to eat our dinner down at the beach and dip our toes in the water. It’s beginning to feel like our tradition of welcoming spring/summer. 

Except I hear we are supposed to have a snow storm this week 😒. Michigan… you really make us pay for the beautiful summers you give.

This is what a full time SAHM & full time business owner looks like. To be honest, I love and hate this picture that my husband took of me. I love that my babies want to be close and want to be held all the time…But I hate that a lot of times I’m also having to work while holding them. 

This year I’m prioritizing learning where I can put boundaries to have better separation. But I remember someone telling me I will never feel 100% with either. When I’m feeling great about family I will feel like I’m failing my business and visa versa. It’s true. 

I started with trying to have “work hours” but then one thing after another has gone wrong (like loosing my entire website, being google banned 🙄 because of a hacker, and having to start from scratch because I RELY on google and my website) forcing me to work around the clock just to keep my business running. 

If you are a full time business owner, who is also home with your babies and you feel like you’ve got SOME sort of a grasp on boundaries. Please share! I don’t want to work my kids childhoods away. 

End of rant.
Just because. I had a few minutes at the studio with the boys while we were waiting for daddy 💙💙

It feels like warm weather has officially arrived and might stick around for a few months. I switched out our seasonal clothes yesterday, which is always like Christmas morning and heartbreaking at the same time. It’s when I realize just how much my kiddos have grown over the winter. I put things in storage that were too big to find them snug now. 

This might sound silly but I hesitantly put these rompers on the boys hoping I could get just ONE more season out of them… and they fit!! On the last buttons and JUST barely fitting… this will be our third summer out of them (yay for clothes that hold up!!). With each of the kiddos there has been one or two outfits that were special. I don’t know what makes them special. Maybe the memories made in them??? Can other mommas relate?? Is this just me?? But it’s so much harder when I have to put these outfits away for the last time. I will hold on to them forever.
Finding bugs. Playing with them. “Loving” on and baby talking to them…and then the inevitable death. Repeat.  #summer

I read something yesterday that was questioning whether moms who are not “in the throes” of motherhood should be celebrated on Mother’s Day. Like if your kiddos are grown… you somehow aren’t as important…and this day isn’t for you? It struck me wrong TBH but I was shocked and a little saddened to see how many in the comments agreed with this.

I don’t believe Mother’s Day is only for mothers who are in the thick of raising little kids…there are SO many things society uses to measure how “mother” you are. (Before I go further obviously every family can celebrate (or not) they way they want.) Everyone’s situation and relationships look different and MOTHERING is different for everyone. In my journey alone I’ve been; a pet mother, plant mother, infertility-with-empty-arms mother, hopeful mother, not-so-hopeful mother, devastated mother, adoptive mother, transracial mother, twin mother, laboring mother, c-section mother, breastfeeding mother, bottle and formula feeding mother, co-sleeping mother, baby led weaning mother, baby food mother, working mother, SAH mother, heart-breaking-as-my-kids-get-older mother, heart-bursting-as-my-kids-get-older mother… this is just ME. Every season I’ve been just as “mother” as the last. Each just as important. 

My momma might be done raising me (or is she?🤪) but she’s BEEN THROUGH IT and is now on MY journey with me. She continues to be there for me in all my big moments AND she nurtures and helps raise my babies. How could I say “you are no longer a mother who can be celebrated on Mother’s Day?” 🤯 does the mom job ever truly end?

And because I know how society is these days I feel I need to repeat… every family is different. Celebrate or don’t. You do you. But I couldn’t just leave my thoughts to myself… #merica 🤪😂 

Oh, Happy Mother’s Day to my mom. 😘

It occurred to me the other day that one day (too soon) all of my babies will be out of the house during the day and while I know they will come back home after school… I realized that the chaos that drives me bonkers through the day won’t be here and I legitimately sobbed. How can something so overwhelming be something I KNOW I will miss. 

Our babies are such a gift. Our time with them like this is SO short. It almost seems cruel. I’m constantly reminded just how precious this season is.
Just a typical morning trying to have breakfast in peace.
Last time we tried to get away I ended up sick and two sick babies at home so our getaway was cut short. This is our retry and so far so good!! 🙏

Welp. We did in fact survive her first year of school. She is still my sassy, fashion loving, artsy, snuggly, mommas girl… but with a lot less teeth. 

We learned that she LOOOOOVES learning. Like sobbed if she had to stay home because she was sick… her teacher offered to let her come to summer school, not because she needs it, but because she knew she would LOVE it and maybe is a little concerned she won’t make it the whole summer without school 😂😂

She is CONSTANTLY writing books. Stitches, staples, or tapes the pages together and everything. Her stories are fun! When I ask her what she wants to be when she grows up she says “ I want to be two things! I want to be a midwife (she’s been saying that for years) and “I want to do patography with you! I want to work with you on your work!” (I can only hope!)

I don’t know where she will land in life but I think she’s gonna be alright. 🥹

Whitford brought his piggy to me yesterday and said “I don’t need piggy anymore, you can take him to the studio” 

Let me back up. He doesn’t go anywhere without his piggy. So this made me super sad. I wasn’t ready for piggy to done. 

Every year I try to take pictures of the kids with something that they currently love. This year was supposed to be piggy. So I said “oh no!! I need to take your picture with piggy first!” So I took him to the studio asap to snap a few. 

On our way home he said “I still love piggy. He loves me. He wants to sleep with me still”

So crisis averted. For now.

we came home to a completely destroyed and flooded house. If we are friends on Facebook, you got some of the details last night… Long story short we ended up at @hamptonmanistee for the night and they were nothing short of a blessing. The ladies were kind and welcoming, they situated us quickly and even upgraded us to a view room that made the kids so happy! Their favorite park and beach are right out our window. 

The employee shifts changed, but the kindness continued this am as I struggled to get the kids ready for school and out the door the woman working the breakfast area helped make sure my kids were fed and happy. 

I honestly could cry at how awesome they have made this awful experience and how accommodating they have been. Thank you so much to the wonderful staff at @hamptonmanistee !!

(My new office view) You guys… I’m overwhelmed with the generosity of friends and strangers both locally and far away. The prayers, concerns, kind words, and offers for help in various capacities has truly touched me and I am thankful for every single person who has reached out, left a prayer, a comment, a message… so so thankful you guys. 

Logically I know this will all get sorted out. I’m not super worried. For those who have asked; We are still waiting to hear the extent of it all but right now it seems the floors in bathroom on the top floor, maybe boys room will be gutted. The kitchen, butlers pantry, and dining room on the main floor, and basement  living room, play room, and laundry room will all be gutted down to the bones. Floors included. A water line busted in the bathroom on the top floor while we were out of town for the weekend. I’m shocked at the amount of water that was in the house from such a little line TBH. 

Emotionally… I’m struggling hard. Every time I go into the house to sort through more items or find something the kids asked for… I see their art projects, salt dough hand prints, and favorite toys just sitting in nasty brown water half buried in soggy plaster… and I burst into uncontrollable tears. Most of it is not salvageable. 

I see where they left their pots of dirt, shovels, bikes… all the remnants of summer play, abandoned as if they were just “taking a break” as they put it. But it’s likely they won’t be back to play this season.

The kids know that mommy and daddy are sad, but they are living their best lives in a nice hotel that has all day access to their favorite park. We will likely be here for maybe two weeks while our insurance gets us set up with a more permanent situation. 

I told the kids that God will turn this into something beautiful. It might take a long time. To remember my words. So that when they face hard things as adults they will remember how God turned a sad situation into something new and good.
I just wanted to give this it’s own spot on my feed. Because it’s happy. And I’m impressed with how well my kids pulled this off 😘

❤️ We finally have a place to move into this Friday! The hotel staff has been such a blessing to us. They’ve been so gracious and accommodating. But it’s been a lot for all six of us being on top of each other 24/7 so we are all very excited to be able to move out. 

Little silver linings keep popping up throughout this experience. New (and better) habits formed in the hotel, a better understanding of each other and how to handle certain.. eh hem melt downs… little things that I hope we carry with us into this new chapter. 

We are focussing on the good that will come out of this and are so thankful that we are all healthy and safe.
My babies. My daughters. I love them more than they could ever know.

I read a conversation about contact sleeping and all the benefits that it can provide. Of course it was talking about babies… 😂 my three year old didn’t get THAT memo. 

Also the second pic… “mommy! Come play with us! We are on the stairs!” This doesn’t look like trouble at all. 🤷🏻‍♀️
Sunday stroll… with a three year old.

Annnnnd because we clean up alright 😂 I was definitely NOT feeling like taking family pics this year, I am exhausted, overwhelmed, frustrated… but I also knew that if I didn’t, I would regret it. So I drug everyone to the studio to do some self portraits. 

Honestly, it was as bad as expected. 😂 BUT look at those precious faces!! They don’t know the turmoil thats happening in my mind and body. They just know that I am their entire world (for a little longer). I pray that they feel loved to the ends of the earth by me. 

As hard as it was, I am 1000% glad that I decided to do these pictures. 

This season is just that… A season. I barely have the energy to pull myself out of bed on some days, but by capturing images like this… I am capturing little bits of joy in a season where I might be too tired to notice it.

I did not expect this picture while we were taking them. This picture does not depict how I was feeling, but at the same time it does. I SEE how much I adore my children and how they still light up being with me and their carefree personalities and smiles of sunshine. I felt heavy behind my smile. This picture is a gift because I won’t always feel this way, and it will forever live on my wall as a reminder of the joy and love that exists, always. Even when I’m not feeling it.

Happy pictures! After 16 weeks of nothing moving forward… abatement is done!! Mitigation will do a little more work and then we can finally start putting the house back together. 🙌🏼 

Thank you to those of you who recommended we hire a public adjuster. We found someone that we feel confident in and I’m excited to be able to hand all of this off to someone else. 

Thank you to everyone who’s been praying for this situation. I am definitely feeling the weight beginning lift!
